# Scratch / diagnostic scripts

When you need a throwaway script to investigate something (compare fits, probe
data shapes, sanity-check a calculation, etc.), put it in the **`ai-scratch/`**
folder — never the repository root.

- `ai-scratch/` is git-ignored (except its `README.md`), so scratch files never
  clutter the project root or show up in `git status`.
- Use clear names like `ai-scratch/diag_model.py`.
- These files are disposable; clean them up when you're done with them.
